1
00:01:07,880 --> 00:01:09,960
[Episode 15:
Go On With Hyaluronic Acid Injections]

2
00:01:16,205 --> 00:01:17,363
Mom!

3
00:01:17,363 --> 00:01:18,386
Yeah.

4
00:01:18,386 --> 00:01:19,408
It smells so good!

5
00:01:19,408 --> 00:01:21,520
- Take it. Share it.
- Okay, thank you.

6
00:01:21,520 --> 00:01:24,200
Are you coming to see me tonight? Right there.

7
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:26,246
[Nanwan Liangpi]
I'm running a stall!

8
00:01:29,920 --> 00:01:31,900
Pay me, missy.

9
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:34,427
- Do your best.
- I will.

10
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:40,319
It's about to start.
Let's go check the sound effects.

11
00:01:40,319 --> 00:01:41,475
Let's go.

12
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:51,120
What took you so long, superstar?

13
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:52,159
I'm sorry.

14
00:01:52,159 --> 00:01:53,719
My assistant is on leave.

15
00:01:53,719 --> 00:01:54,996
No driver.

16
00:01:54,996 --> 00:01:56,799
I had a traffic jam.

17
00:01:56,799 --> 00:01:59,079
I'll make believe.

18
00:01:59,079 --> 00:02:00,480
What do you mean?

19
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:02,040
Why are you pretending?

20
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:03,040
If you had an assistant,

21
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:05,495
the three of us would have a meal together.

22
00:02:05,495 --> 00:02:06,920
Late is late.

23
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:09,039
Unprofessional is unprofessional.
Why are you lying?

24
00:02:09,039 --> 00:02:11,200
I'm not. I'm an actor.

25
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:12,360
It's normal to have one.

26
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:14,479
You take yourself as a superstar.

27
00:02:14,479 --> 00:02:17,185
If you had a role, would you still be here?

28
00:02:18,334 --> 00:02:19,960
Fine. I won't be here anymore.

29
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:21,695
I'll get my assistant to do my makeup.

30
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:37,120
Where's Zhu Qiao Fei?

31
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:39,840
I don't know.
I called him, but he didn't answer.

32
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:41,032
You get changed first.

33
00:02:41,032 --> 00:02:42,600
I'll look for him.

34
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:43,788
Okay.

35
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:48,142
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

36
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:52,360
- Here you are. Enjoy.
- Thank you.

37
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:54,261
[Hongxia Diner]

38
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,640
I searched everywhere.

39
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:02,639
We're the next!

40
00:03:02,639 --> 00:03:05,240
He's in the first scene!

41
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:06,520
We need a standby.

42
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:08,634
It's too late to find one now.

43
00:03:11,040 --> 00:03:12,680
I'll search again.

44
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:14,360
- Here. Sit.
- Sit.

45
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,922
- Close your eyes!
- What?

46
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:41,040
Go, go.

47
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:43,160
Zhu Qiao Fei is downstairs.

48
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:44,836
How did you...

49
00:03:49,199 --> 00:03:51,960
It's not you, right?

50
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:54,199
You think it's costly,

51
00:03:54,199 --> 00:03:56,858
so you always send long messages, don't you?

52
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:01,522
How did you find the address?

53
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:05,280
This community has the most acacia trees.

54
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:07,201
Since you could
find acacia flowers in the room,

55
00:04:07,201 --> 00:04:08,952
it can't be a high floor.

56
00:04:08,952 --> 00:04:10,440
And then?

57
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:11,640
By knocking and asking.

58
00:04:11,640 --> 00:04:13,008
Do you have any water?

59
00:04:13,008 --> 00:04:16,000
I'm thirsty. I want juice.

60
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,304
Drink later.

61
00:04:17,304 --> 00:04:18,680
We promised to go to the temple fair.

62
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:19,720
Let's go.

63
00:04:19,720 --> 00:04:21,012
Wait for me.

64
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:27,896
I told you he wouldn't go.

65
00:04:35,519 --> 00:04:36,740
Let's go.

66
00:04:42,319 --> 00:04:45,016
I got my phone and luggage.

67
00:04:46,872 --> 00:04:48,446
What about the writing class?

68
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:52,276
I don't need it to win the gold prize.

69
00:04:53,840 --> 00:04:55,728
- Let's go.
- Go.

70
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,926
Father,

71
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:13,280
now that I'm in disguise,

72
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:15,008
I think it's just so-so.

73
00:05:15,008 --> 00:05:17,422
You should agree to let me go.

74
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:20,690
You may go.

75
00:05:21,399 --> 00:05:23,729
Zhu Qiao Fei!

76
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:28,200
Zhu Qiao Fei!

77
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:30,319
Excuse me! Excuse me!

78
00:05:30,319 --> 00:05:32,127
Zhu Qiao Fei!

79
00:05:32,839 --> 00:05:34,250
Where is he?

80
00:05:34,839 --> 00:05:36,520
It's your turn.

81
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:38,079
<i>Sis, don't be angry.</i>

82
00:05:38,079 --> 00:05:40,120
<i>I'm looking for him.</i>

83
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:42,072
<i>Just hold on.</i>

84
00:05:42,680 --> 00:05:45,105
I'm dressed as Ma Wen Cai.

85
00:05:45,696 --> 00:05:47,666
<i>Then let Ma Wen Cai go first.</i>

86
00:05:54,879 --> 00:05:58,000
On my long way to Hangzhou for study,

87
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,800
I immerse myself in literature

88
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:01,755
to ease my sorrow.

89
00:06:05,128 --> 00:06:06,320
Why are you here?

90
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:07,764
It's a long story.

91
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:11,080
Bro, are you going to school?

92
00:06:11,080 --> 00:06:13,959
Since we met, I'd like to join you.

93
00:06:13,959 --> 00:06:15,160
That'd be wonderful.

94
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:17,640
May I know your esteemed name?

95
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:20,501
I'm Ma Wen Cai from the capital.

96
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:22,320
Get off!

97
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:24,240
Look at them.

98
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:25,560
Not good at all.

99
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:27,383
Go and practice more.

100
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:31,224
Where is she?

101
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:36,520
Zhu Qiao Fei, you bastard! Go back with me!

102
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:37,879
I'm waiting for my assistant. I can't...

103
00:06:37,879 --> 00:06:39,519
I don't care if you have one!

104
00:06:39,519 --> 00:06:41,225
Do you ever know it?

105
00:06:41,805 --> 00:06:43,759
Your grip is too strong!

106
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:47,922
I need to finish to get the final payment!

107
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:51,319
You're not performing.

108
00:06:51,319 --> 00:06:52,800
You're acting like a diva!

109
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:54,160
I really can't do it!

110
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:55,383
Look.

111
00:06:56,960 --> 00:06:58,200
When I auditioned this morning,

112
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,960
I found I was allergic to glue.

113
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:02,110
It only got better after
I went to the hospital for an IV drip.

114
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:04,600
I thought it wouldn't happen tonight.

115
00:07:05,399 --> 00:07:06,439
I'm sorry.

116
00:07:06,439 --> 00:07:08,835
Couldn't you tell me earlier?

117
00:07:10,056 --> 00:07:11,399
Alright.

118
00:07:11,399 --> 00:07:12,720
I'm also at fault.

119
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,240
I apologize.

120
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:15,685
Let's go.

121
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,176
I'm allergic.

122
00:07:18,176 --> 00:07:20,520
I brought several types of glue.

123
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:22,319
At least one will do.

124
00:07:22,319 --> 00:07:23,920
What if none?

125
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:25,920
Bro, at such a distance,

126
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:27,680
no one can see!

127
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:29,676
What are you dawdling for?

128
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,839
I lied.

129
00:07:33,839 --> 00:07:35,025
I know.

130
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:38,165
I promise you, only I know it.

131
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:44,802
An actor with stage fright?

132
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:47,142
In this industry,

133
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:50,182
I've been an extra for four or five years.

134
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:52,279
Later a company signed me...

135
00:07:52,279 --> 00:07:55,759
At this moment, you're telling a story?

136
00:07:55,759 --> 00:07:56,960
Later,

137
00:07:56,960 --> 00:07:58,920
I played the third male lead.

138
00:07:58,920 --> 00:08:00,959
I worked really hard.

139
00:08:00,959 --> 00:08:02,828
I went on a promo tour with them.

140
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:05,759
A viewer asked me.

141
00:08:05,759 --> 00:08:08,786
I was happy, until I heard him say,

142
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:12,199
"Don't you think you tried too hard?"

143
00:08:12,199 --> 00:08:14,160
I replied, "Sorry."

144
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:16,960
"I wanted to do my best."

145
00:08:16,960 --> 00:08:18,839
"So I tried too hard."

146
00:08:18,839 --> 00:08:20,185
He said,

147
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:23,768
"Try harder to
augment your nasal bridge first."

148
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:26,630
Everyone laughed.

149
00:08:28,536 --> 00:08:30,616
I had no choice but to laugh with them.

150
00:08:36,559 --> 00:08:40,040
I changed my painting to earn 300 yuan.

151
00:08:40,040 --> 00:08:43,367
For the final payment of KT panels,
I looked for you.

152
00:08:43,367 --> 00:08:45,080
And someone ghosted my game bill.

153
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:48,080
Even so, my link remains, you know?

154
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:50,159
Should I give up painting
because of their bad taste?

155
00:08:50,159 --> 00:08:52,360
Should I cancel my link
because my bill is ghosted?

156
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:54,159
And should you, an actor,

157
00:08:54,159 --> 00:08:56,080
stop acting because someone criticized you?

158
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:58,840
But I got hyaluronic acid injections later.

159
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:00,919
I spent all my savings on learning acting.

160
00:09:00,919 --> 00:09:03,320
- But I was still criticized.
- Then go on.

161
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:05,639
Go on with hyaluronic acid injections,
learning acting,

162
00:09:05,639 --> 00:09:08,200
being criticized, and acting!

163
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:10,000
If you escape pain,

164
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:11,738
how far can you go?

165
00:09:12,519 --> 00:09:16,320
An escape can also be painful.

166
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:17,635
Darn it.

167
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:20,072
You're scolding me?

168
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:22,720
I knew your Taiwanese accent was fake.

169
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:25,308
You made me curse.

170
00:09:25,896 --> 00:09:27,254
Let's go.

171
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,380
Seriously...

172
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:32,625
Are you okay?

173
00:09:34,399 --> 00:09:36,833
How am I supposed to act now?

174
00:09:41,560 --> 00:09:42,879
Forget it.

175
00:09:42,879 --> 00:09:44,689
My card is cancelled.

176
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:47,280
No final payment.

177
00:09:47,280 --> 00:09:49,519
Liang Shan Bo sprained his ankle.

178
00:09:49,519 --> 00:09:52,358
Ma Wen Cai married Zhu Ying Tai.

179
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,410
It's all your fault.

180
00:09:56,040 --> 00:09:58,608
How about... taking off?

181
00:09:58,608 --> 00:09:59,679
What?

182
00:09:59,679 --> 00:10:00,989
Hurry, hurry!

183
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:05,867
Wait! I have something to report.

184
00:10:08,039 --> 00:10:09,741
Do you have a wedding scene?

185
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:13,039
It just happened as we improvised.

186
00:10:13,039 --> 00:10:16,240
It turned out to be Liang Shan Bo.

187
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:21,060
He wants to discuss with Ma Wen Cai his...

188
00:10:23,519 --> 00:10:24,679
The thousand tael of silver

189
00:10:24,679 --> 00:10:26,120
is my betrothal gift.

190
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:27,456
Ying Tai and I studied together

191
00:10:27,456 --> 00:10:29,200
since we were young.

192
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:30,472
When she saw me off for 18 miles,

193
00:10:30,472 --> 00:10:32,080
we were secretly engaged.

194
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:34,360
I beg for your support.

195
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:35,639
It's so...

196
00:10:35,639 --> 00:10:38,799
After all, Ma Wen Cai is of noble birth.

197
00:10:38,799 --> 00:10:41,480
How could he suffer such injustice?

198
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:43,210
So preposterous!

199
00:10:43,210 --> 00:10:44,960
The gleaming tael of silver

200
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:47,519
speaks louder than Three Letters and Six Rites!

201
00:10:47,519 --> 00:10:50,738
Zhu Ying Tai trotted to mediate.

202
00:10:52,650 --> 00:10:55,920
Shan Bo, though we've been secretly engaged,

203
00:10:55,920 --> 00:10:58,260
Master Wen Cai
offers Three Letters and Six Rites

204
00:10:58,260 --> 00:10:59,600
for a proper, formal marriage.

205
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:01,200
Such a farce

206
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,895
is unseemly.

207
00:11:04,559 --> 00:11:06,159
If you leave,

208
00:11:06,159 --> 00:11:08,880
my family will be shamed.

209
00:11:08,880 --> 00:11:12,880
What... what should they do?

210
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:14,360
What's going on?

211
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:16,410
She can't improvise anymore.

212
00:11:23,560 --> 00:11:25,799
Red candles flicker, with a homeland dream.

213
00:11:25,799 --> 00:11:28,159
Romance may mislead a hero.

214
00:11:28,159 --> 00:11:30,559
If we become sworn brothers,

215
00:11:30,559 --> 00:11:34,159
we may work wonders on the battlefield!

216
00:11:34,159 --> 00:11:37,520
They untie the red ribbon, fold it,

217
00:11:37,520 --> 00:11:40,200
and swear to the heavens!

218
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,799
I, Liang Shan Bo,

219
00:11:41,799 --> 00:11:43,200
I, Ma Wen Cai,

220
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,840
I, Zhu Ying Tai,

221
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:47,411
hereby become sworn brothers!

222
00:11:47,411 --> 00:11:49,040
Together, we shall face the nation's crisis

223
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:51,264
and leave our names in history!

224
00:11:52,040 --> 00:11:53,679
Quick, play the clapping sound I prepared.

225
00:11:53,679 --> 00:11:54,759
- Wonderful!
- Good!

226
00:11:54,759 --> 00:11:55,915
Go.

227
00:11:59,559 --> 00:12:01,360
Wonderful!

228
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:02,519
Good job.

229
00:12:02,519 --> 00:12:04,865
- Good job.
- Interesting.

230
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:26,000
Hello?

231
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,440
<i>Why are you running away?</i>

232
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:29,520
<i>You ungrateful brat!</i>

233
00:12:29,520 --> 00:12:31,200
You don't want me there.

234
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:32,760
<i>We don't?</i>

235
00:12:32,760 --> 00:12:35,440
<i>I bought you milk to boost your brain.</i>

236
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:36,570
<i>But you ran off without a word!</i>

237
00:12:36,570 --> 00:12:37,840
You...

238
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:39,120
You bought milk?

239
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:40,280
Are you his dad?

240
00:12:40,280 --> 00:12:41,480
You don't even know he's lactose intolerant...

241
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:43,399
<i>- Who are you?</i>
- And burned the back of his hand...

242
00:12:43,399 --> 00:12:44,952
<i>What? You...</i>

243
00:12:45,519 --> 00:12:47,590
You're fiercer than my dad.

244
00:12:48,399 --> 00:12:50,405
We might miss the show.

245
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:52,980
We can see fireworks.

246
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:56,003
What if we miss the fireworks too?

247
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:02,678
Forget it. I'm unlucky anyway.

248
00:13:33,320 --> 00:13:34,560
It's really there.

249
00:13:34,560 --> 00:13:35,992
You lose your Taiwanese accent

250
00:13:35,992 --> 00:13:37,159
when you woke up, right?

251
00:13:37,159 --> 00:13:38,957
It's there!

252
00:13:56,280 --> 00:13:57,720
I have burn ointment at home.

253
00:13:57,720 --> 00:13:59,349
I'll get some for you.

254
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:15,126
I have xerophthalmia.

255
00:14:16,760 --> 00:14:19,105
I'll get you some eye drops too.

256
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:21,449
Thank you.

257
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:29,240
<i>In the world,</i>

258
00:14:29,240 --> 00:14:31,960
<i>nothing is more stupid than fireworks.</i>

259
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:33,300
<i>If there is,</i>

260
00:14:33,920 --> 00:14:35,206
<i>it must be me.</i>

261
00:14:35,880 --> 00:14:37,479
<i>This moment</i>

262
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:41,919
<i>is worth everything.</i>

263
00:14:41,919 --> 00:14:44,054
Ren Xi Zhou!
